<dl id="n40055b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40055b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40055b"> 55(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> energumens</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">This theory of disease disappeared sooner than did the belief in possession; the energumens of the early Christian church, who were under the care of a special clerical order of exorcists, testify to a belief in possession; but the demon theory of disease receives no recognition; the energumens find their analogues in the converts of missionaries in China, Africa and elsewhere. <small> &ldquo;DEMONOLOGY&rdquo; <a name="EBDY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDY"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
